By Udora Orizu The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila, has condoled with President Muhammadu Buhari and the members of his extended family over the demise of his nephew, Alhaji Mutari Dauda. The Speaker also prayed for the repose of Daudaâ€™s soul, who was the younger brother to Mamman Daura. Gbajabiamila, in a condolence message issued on Saturday by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Lanre Lasisi, extended his condolences to the entire people of Daura Emirate over the loss. He prayed that Almighty Allah will give the president, members of his extended family and the Daura Emirate the fortitude to bear the loss.